            <title>[CASSANDRA-13868] Safely handle empty buffers when outputting to JSON</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-13868</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As discussed in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-13734&quot; title=&quot;BufferUnderflowException when using uppercase UUID&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-13734&quot;&gt;CASSANDRA-13734&lt;/a&gt;, when &lt;tt&gt;Selection#rowToJSON&lt;/tt&gt; encounters an empty &lt;tt&gt;ByteBuffer&lt;/tt&gt;, a &lt;tt&gt;BufferUnderflowException&lt;/tt&gt; can be thrown. At a minimum let&apos;s be defensive and not throw an error.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
